cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of occlusion in face recognition, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach for recognition using structured sparsity, which involves optimization techniques and dictionary learning. This makes it relevant to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the issue of security in face recognition, which could make it relevant to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
